ffuser stands in the foreground on a glass table. The woman turns toward it and extends her arm, holding a small remote control. Gray text appears on the right: “LARGE LIBRARY OF SCENTS.” She points the remote toward the diffuser, suggesting she is activating or adjusting it.\n\nA series of elegant hotel-like interiors follows. One is a spacious lounge with tall windows, white curtains, soft seating, plants, large pendant lights, and a large graphic portrait at the far end. Over the center appears a black label reading “Top Scents,” then “MY WAY,” with smaller text beneath: “Inspired by 1 Hotel.” Another refined lobby-like room appears with symmetrical chairs, a chandelier, polished floors, and an abstract artwork at the back. Its label reads “Top Scents,” “DREAM ON,” and “Inspired by Westin Hotels.” A third luxury lounge appears with patterned black-and-white wall panels, high ceilings, white sofas, and tables. Its label reads “Top Scents,” “24K MAGIC,” and “Inspired by W Hotel.” A QR code labeled “SCAN ME” appears at the lower right and remains through much of the rest of the commercial.\n\nThe man reappears in a sleek kitchen or open living area with matte gray cabinetry, built-in appliances, and a light stone or concrete wall. He stands near a counter, facing forward with his hands together, speaking calmly. The “25% OFF USE CODE: DJ25” text remains in the upper left, and the QR code with “SCAN ME” remains at the lower right.\n\nA close view presents a black Aroma360 diffuser on a countertop. It is tall, cylindrical, and slim, standing on a round base. A small rectangular remote lies on the counter beside it. White text to the right reads “COLD AIR DIFFUSION.” The background is softly blurred, with the kitchen area and a plant visible.\n\nThe man is then seen smiling and laughing with the same woman in the modern kitchen area. He stands on the left in his dark jacket, and she stands on the right, now wearing a tan or golden-brown top. Both face each other with open, cheerful expressions. The top of a black diffuser is visible between them near the bottom of the image, reinforcing that the product is part of the space.\n\nA silver cylindrical diffuser is shown again on a glass table in front of the white tufted sofa, with a remote control placed beside it. The device is upright and cleanly designed, matching the bright, minimalist décor.\n\nThe woman and man sit together on the white sofa. She holds the silver diffuser upright in one hand as if showing it, while he sits beside her in a black outfit, hands together, watching her. On the glass table in front of them are additional Aroma360 items, including a black diffuser and small scent bottles. The woman then holds a small clear bottle close to her nose and smells it, eyes relaxed. White text appears beside her: “HEALTHY LUXURY SCENTING.” Her dark nail polish is visible as she grips the bottle.\n\nThe image fades through a soft white wash, then both people are seated side by side on the sofa again, facing forward. The woman sits on the left, composed and attentive; the man sits on the right, gesturing as he speaks. On the glass table in front of them are the silver and black cylindrical diffusers and several small clear bottles arranged neatly. A dark rectangular website graphic appears across the lower center reading “aroma360.com,” with a visible cursor pointer nearby. The QR code remains at the lower right.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean off-white promotional card. Centered near the top is the Aroma360 logo. Large black text reads “25% OFF,” with “USE CODE: DJ25” underneath. To the right is a QR code labeled “SCAN ME.”",
